dom australia hong kong india new zealand singapore thailand canada colombia dominican republic jamaica jersey mexico nova scotia panama quebec george n hatsopoulos  wikipedia george n hatsopoulos from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search george n hatsopoulos george hatsopoulos  chemical heritage foundation born  january   age  athens greece fields mechanical engineering institutions massachusetts institute of technology notable awards john fritz medal  george nicholas hatsopoulos born january   is a greek american mechanical engineer noted for his work in thermodynamics and for having cofounded thermo electron contents  early life  hatsopouloskeenan reformulation of thermodynamics  overview  see also  references  external links early lifeedit hatsopoulos was born in athens greece in  and is related tohow the former rector of the athens polytechnic school nicolas kitsikis he attended athens polytechnic before entering mit where received his bachelor and master of science  mechanical engineer  and doctorate of science  hatsopouloskeenan reformulation of thermodynamicsedit in  he and joseph keenan published their textbook principles of general thermodynamics which restates the second law of thermodynamics in terms of the existence of stable equilibrium states their formulation of the second law of thermodynamics states that “ when an isolated system performs a process after the removal of a series of internal constraints it will reach a unique state of equilibrium this state of equilibrium is independent of the order in which the constraints are removed ” the hatsopouloskeenan statement of the second law entails the clausius kelvinplanck and carathéodory statements of the second law and has provided a basis to extend the traditional definition of entropy to the nonequilibrium domain in  hatsopoulos also contributed to a formulation of a unified theory of mechanics and thermodynamics arguably a precursor of the emerging field of quantum thermodynamics overviewedit while at mit hatsopoulos was head of the engineering division of matrad corporation new york matrad corporation and mit financially supported his doctoral thesis the thermoelectron engine matrad corporation was owned by the family of peter m nomikos a harvard business school graduate in  nomikos cofounded with hatsopoulos the thermo electron corporation thermo electron became a major provider of analytical instruments and services for a variety of domains under the development of george hatsopoulos john hatsopoulos and arvin smith in  george hatsopoulos was president of the thermo electron engineering corporation and senior lecturer in mechanical engineering at mit in  hatsopoulos won the john fritz medal which is the highest american award in the engineering profession and presented each year for scientific or industrial achievement in any field of pure or applied science in  he was awarded the rd annual heinz award in technology the economy and employment mr hatsopoulos is also a recipient of the international center in new yorks award of excellence in  along with arvin smith and john hatsopoulos he was awarded the  pittcon heritage award from the chemical heritage foundation see alsoedit history of thermodynamics referencesedit    a b mit  appointments to administrative positions and four faculty changes announced the tech lxxvi no   httptechmiteduvpdfnpdf  hatsopoulos george n keenan joseph h  principles of general thermodynamics john wiley  sons inc ccn  cs maint multiple names authors list link  gyftopoulos elias p beretta gian paolo  thermodynamics foundations and applications dover pu inc isbn    see eg httpwwwquantumthermodynamicsorg  hatsopoulos george nicholas  the thermoelectron engine doctoral dissertation massachusetts institute of technology cambridge massachusetts usa httphdlhandlenet  it dont mean a thing if you aint got that green hbs and the birth of venture capital hbs bulletin online december  httpwwwalumnihbsedubulletindecember